commitResults.messageBody:
Implemented Level-7 Save.

Adds new class Storage.java to handle storage.

Saves tasks to ./data/xiaobai.txt, and loads tasks on startup.
Automatically saves tasks after add/mark/unmark/delete commands.

Level-7: Save

Implement persistence so that tasks are saved to disk and reloaded on startup.

- Adds Storage.java for file I/O with ./data/xiaobai.txt
- Loads tasks at startup, creates folder/file if missing
- Auto-saves after task mutations (add, mark, unmark, delete)
- Handles corrupted lines gracefully by skipping and warning user

Implement Level-8:

- DateTimeUtil: lenient parsing
- Deadline & Event store LocalDateTime and print human-friendly dates
- Storage saves & loads timestamps and remains backward compatible
- Commands keep existing syntax; optional 'on <date>' filter"

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge branch 'branch-Level-8' for Level-8: Dates and Times

commitResults.messageBody:
Refactor app into a clearer OOP design

- Extract classes:
  - Ui (user interactions)
  - Storage (load/save to ./data/xiaobai.txt)
  - Parser (parses input and returns Command objects)
  - TaskList (encapsulates task collection and operations)
- Introduce Command classes: AddTodo, AddDeadline, AddEvent, List, Mark, Unmark, Delete, Bye
  (+ On command for date filtering as a stretch)
- Rework main loop in XiaoBai to: read -> Parser.parse() -> Command.execute(tasks, ui, storage)

Restructure source tree into clear Java packages (no behavior changes).

- Keep source root at src/main/java
- Introduce package hierarchy
- Add/adjust package declarations and imports across files
- Update entry point to xiaobai.XiaoBai

Add JUnit 5 test classes to verify key functionalities in XiaoBai:
- ParserTest: ensures Parser.parse() correctly interprets commands
  (todo, deadline, event, bye, and invalid input cases)
- TaskListTest: validates TaskList.deleteTask() behavior, including
  deletion of first, middle, last tasks and invalid indices

commitResults.messageTitle: A-Jar: Package app as executable JAR
commitResults.messageBody: Configur build system to produce an executable JAR for XiaoBai
Add JavaDoc-style header comments to most public classes and methods
Tweak the code to comply with a coding standard

Give users a way to find a task by searching for a keyword in the task description.
- Add FindCommand class to search tasks by keyword in description
- Update Parser to support "find <keyword>" user input

Add GUI for XiaoBai

Implement a basic JavaFX graphical user interface to replace the
text-based UI.

- Add Main, MainWindow, DialogBox classes and corresponding FXML
  files for the GUI layout.
- Implement GuiUi to accumulate chatbot responses for display in the
  GUI.
- Updat XiaoBai with getResponse(...) to support interaction via the
  GUI.
- Integrate user and bot dialog images for a more engaging UI.
